<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">8621.01/274a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-05T17:00:00-04:00">September 5, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>76. Associated press telegram from Tokyo under date September 1st reports
                            that the Japanese Navy Office issued a statement to vernacular <pb facs="0855" n="753" xml:id="pg_753"/> newspapers in regard to
                            Japanese harbor works in the Mandated Pacific Islands part of which read
                            “Those islands are Japanese territory”. Telegraph whether this
                            translation is accurate and send full Japanese text by pouch.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>